description: When Archie's dad gets a new job, the Andrews have to leave town, and all of his friends are distraught to see him go! Later, as the Andrews family goes house-hunting, the memories continue between Archie and his parents. It becomes more and more apparent how much the fabric of Riverdale has been woven into the family's life. With emotions running high, can they go through with the move?
name: Goodbye Forever Part 3

description: Archie's dad's promotion requires the Andrews to move out of town. A fortuitous trip to a hamburger joint in their new home town seems eerily like Pop Tate's, right down to the teens who hang out there! This slice of reality pie has Archie and his family thinking... is this move the right move? Will they tough it out and try out life in a new town after all, or reconsider and move back to Riverdale? It's the conclusion to the most poignant 'New Look' story yet , rendered in the 'realistic' art style.
name: Goodbye Forever Part 4

description:
The Past 

In an art class there is a replacement male model for the usual female ones. A young Katchoo's artwork is singled out as getting the idea. The Artist takes her to one side and offers her a sponsorship and a show in Houston. It takes all his persistence to get her to agree. 
 
When she calmly reveals she has an art show at dinner that night Francine's excitement is infections and Katchoo actually gets excited too. As Fran runs around looking for clothes to wear she poses with handfuls of clothes in her hand and underwear. Just as Katchoo complains to David about always having to draw men when she needs a real muse. Francie is very hesitant but the love and importance of it means she agrees to model. 

 
Flash Forward

A red faced Francie has been crying in her bed again, she comes down to her mother and  Katchoo.
name: If I Wake Up

description:
Flash Forward 

Katchoo and Francine hardly speak while Francine's daughter is in the kitchen with them. Francine showers and when Marie takes her upstairs the two go out and talk in the yard. Katchoo thinks her friend looks warn down beyond her years.  
 
Katchoo confirms it was her at the lake the other day she came for her mothers funeral and stopped by. She tells her about the phone numbers and when asked about David she says nothing. Eventually she says that yes they married in Hawaii and lived there as they planned. 

 
The Past 

Katchoo is painting Francine and when she looks she finds the paints more beautiful than she feels. When Katchoo says that what she sees Fran gets annoyed saying that what she wants her to be not who she is and storms off. Whens he locks her door too Katchoo kicks it to splinters with one kick.
name: Nothing Gold Can Stay

description:
A lot of home truths get told when Francine and Katchoo argue about the states of their lives. 
 
In Houston a drunk Katchoo skulks around her own exhibition. David arrives in his usually jolly manner she cuts hims down and stomps away. A beautiful older woman approaches David and asks if that was Katina. When he says it is she gives him her card to give her. It is Carolyn Hobbs of the New Hobbs Foundation wishing to be her benefactor. David is blown away by it. Freddie and Casey appear and she stays with David while Freddie catches up with Katchoo.
 
At the bar Katchoo's is getting more drunk when a  man who looks like John Cleese tries to chat her up and gets shot down swiftly. Freddie start to inquire about Francine but Katchoo is not in the mood for him. 
 
David hears a scream in the galley that sounds like Francine's and he runs toward it.
name: Talk To Me

description:
David, Casey and Freddie find Francine stood in a gallery titled Francine with six foot tall pictures of her in tasteful nude and semi nude poses. Freddie is utterly smitten with them but Francine is angry and crying when an ambivalent and sloshed Katchoo arrives hands in pockets. Francine bawls in her face about the violation she feels. For once Katchoo has nothing much to say. She turns it on David as well and, after attracting a crowd, storms out. 
 
A sullen Katchoo quietly asks David to get her the curator.  When he arrives he refuses to take down the exhibit as she requests so she stuffs his tie in his mouth and calls the office saying the exhibition is receiving obscenity complaints from the police. Casey seeing Freddie's reaction to the massive images of Francine's boobs calls her doctor and schedules an implant size increase procedure. 
 
Carolyn Hobbs sits next to Katchoo and asks if she'd like to be rich, Katchoo says shes been rich. She takes a new tac and asks if she'd like her paintings in the Metropolitan by the end of the year. Is she wants to be a part of art history all she has to do is say yes.
 
Outside Francine's car has been towed. She finds this out from an unseen man who says she is beautiful and his name is Brad. 
 
Back home Francine is packed and moving back to her mothers. David offers to drive her tot he airport when Katchoo fails to say a word. They leave and Katchoo breaks down  never getting further into the house than the doorway.
name: The Silence of Friends

description:
Katchoo has cried all day and David is lost not knowing what to do. He finds Katchoo in the garden with a bottle in the rain and he carries her back inside. 
 
In Tennessee Francine is at her mothers and has slept past noon dreaming of an award ceremony withe Clinton's honoring her and Kat. She wakes she her unopened suitcase and goes back under the covers. Francie floats about as her mothers friends call round and coo over her.
 
Katchoo is a wreck and as she vomits David calls her "Baby". In a weak voice she tells him to never call her that. Later Carolyn rings and Katchoo says she'll take her offer but only for new works and no 'Francine' images at all.
  
Casey gets a huge shock when she walks into the living room and finds one of the six foot 'Francine' exhibit paintings in her living room. She heads over to talk with David, she is upset by Freddie and needs someone to talk with about Freddie and the overweight image of Francie's behind in her livingroom. In her impulsive way she leaps on him crying. Then in a mood swing she rips off her shirt and tries to kiss him. Only to be tapped on the shoulder by a maniacally grinning Katchoo.
name: Years To Go

description:
Francine goes fishing like she did as a child in the river but ends up sitting on the bank thinking about how much simpler life is when you are a child. 
 
Katchoo starts softly enough with Casey but when she has enough she bodily dumps her on the floor. Casey complains so what is he likes David to which Katchoo points out she is Mrs Femur. She then asks of Katchoo can turn her gay as she did it for Francine. Katchoo is stunned for once in her life. Casey says if she can do it for Francine when with Casey and her body it should be easy. She frightens Casey with her predicable rage but takes pity on the fragile creature. 
 
They notice David has been on the phone and is now quiet and is suddenly shaking. 
 
Elsewhere Tambi is with a lawyer who has just told David he has a half share in his sisters wealth. Tambi says he will refuse to take on the partnership aspect of it and he is not like his sister. 
 
David sits stunned and tells the girl in a daze he inherited 1.4.. Casey jumps in  Million?!  David mutters.. 1.4 Billion. Casey in all seriousness says "Take Me!".  David gets a drink and laments his sister did nothing with her money and he will use it to do good and will leave an empty account when he dies. Katchoo kisses him. 
 
Casey gets up when they don't come back in to the room. She hears them in a darkened bedroom and tears roll down her face. She strips and joins them on the bed much to their surprise. She meekly asks if she can join them but Katchoo orders he off and to get dressed. 
 
Seconds later the front door opens and Francine shouts "Hello" they scramble and Katchoo pretends to be asleep in bed as Casey and David hide in the en-suit. Francie comes in and hopes to say her piece to the sleeping Katchoo first. Casey knock something and Fran heads to the bathroom. Katchoo jumps up and heads her off. She says her piece about Katchoo knowing her better than she does herself and Casey adn David tumble out of the bathroom much to Francine's Confusing. Casey sees shes the only one with no clothes on.
name: Fear of Swimming

description:
Freddie is livid when he discovers Francine is having a hot and steamy love affair with a married man. Why couldn't it be him? Little does he know his own wife, Casey, is pursuing another man, David, who only has eyes for Katchoo! Make sense? Of course not! Don't miss this decidedly torrid issue of SIP, guaranteed to raise your blood pressure!

In a police station as soaking Casey accuses Freddie of telling her he paid for the painting of Francine. He claims he paid for it by spending a year with Francine. Francine shouts at him accusing him of being a borderline stalker while Katchoo casually chats with the desk officer.

Francine demands her Polaroids back and Casey wails that he hosed her down. Through the chaos a cop fires a gun and with the sudden quiet Katchoo starts to explain the story to the desk officer

Flashback

Francine, Katchoo, David and Casey are around the able eating and filling Francine in on what was going on. They tease but forgive Casey who suddenly remembers the painting of Francine was her reason for coming in the first place. Katchoo and Francine are stunned but Katchoo not for long and grabs her keys.

Freddie gets home and admires his acquisition until he hears Katchoo's voice. She throws him across the room and collects up all her paintings as Casey sees if he is alright and Francie demands her bikini back. Casey has enough and takes Freddie's Porsche driving it in reverse over neighbors gardens.

Present

Casey and Freddie get held but the rest leave as David and Katchoo discuss flying to New York to sort out the inheritance Francine feels left behind.

In a room Tambi is weight lifting before her on t e wall are three photograph,s two dark haired girls have their faces X'd out with Katchoo's photo in the middle.
name: I, Me, Mine

description:
It's a special summer swimsuit issue! Francine and Katchoo hit the beach on the hot white sands of Florida's Emerald Coast. It's summer vacation, and Katchoo is determined to relax and catch a few rays, but between Francine's shrinking bikini, a raging sandcastle war, and an endless stream of love-struck college boys, Katchoo soon finds there is no rest for the weary or diplomatically challenged.

After the heavy and dark issues of late this month Francine, Katchoo and David hit the beach.

Francine bursts into a house in a panic she dashes to the bathroom failing to even notice a small boy sitting on the floor. His mother walks in and asks him what was that noise, he replies it was a wild lady. As Francie exits the bathroom Katchoo comes to the door and tells her this is the wrong house, Francine explains Katchoo wouldn't stop the car on the way there.

Katchoo abandons the others and heads right for the beach as Francine unpacks. later she and David sit on the sand and talk about Darcy and Emma. David recalls how he'd met Katchoo the night she and Emma fled. Francine is coming down to the beach with food when she sees them rolling in the sand and sadly turns and walks back in. They discuss exciting things to do but settle for sitting in the sun all day instead.
name: Bikini Beach

description:
"Pussycat" is a 1960s character and comicstrip inspired by Playboy's Little Annie Fannie that was featured in various men's magazines published by Martin Goodman (the publisher of Marvel Comics). The character is a secret agent working for S.C.O.R.E. (Secret Council of Ruthless Extroverts) to fight against nemesis organization L.U.S.T. The stories were written by Stan Lee, Larry Lieber, Ernie Hart, and other Marvel Comics Staff. Although the strip was provocative and sexy, it did not show nudity or sex.

This one-shot magazine features a cover by Bill Everett, eight 5-page reprints from the strip, an original story produced for this edition, as well as a centerfold pin-up by Good Girl artist Bill Ward.

  • "The Mirthful Misadventures of a Merry, Mixed-Up Miss!" Art by Wally Wood with retouched art for the reprint by Jim Mooney
    - Reprinted from Male Annual #3 (1965)
  • "The Mirthful Misadventures of a Naughty Nonsensical Nymphet!"
    - Reprinted from Stag Annual #3 (1966)
  • "The Madly Mirthful Misadventures of a Lively Little Lass" Art by Bill Ward
    - Reprinted from Male Annual #4 (1966)
  • "The Cool and Carefree Capers of a Curvy Cuddly Chick" Art by Bill Ward
    - Reprinted from Stag Annual #4 (1967)
  • "The Cavortin' Case Of The Booby-Trapped Bra" Art by Bill Ward
    - Reprinted from Male Annual #5 (1967)
  • "Damsel in Disguise" Art by Bill Ward
    - Reprinted from Stag Annual #5 (1968)
  • "Another Capricious Caper of the Country's Most Cataclysmically Cuddlesome Curvaceous Cutie" Art by Bill Ward
    - Reprinted from Men Annual #2 (1968)
  • "The Madly Mirthful Misadventures of a Most Generously Endowed Modern Miss" Art by Bill Ward
    - Reprinted from Men Annual #1 (1967)
  • "The Hidden Hippie Caper" Art by Jim Mooney
    - Original Story for this edition
name: Pussycat

description: 'High-Scoring Hijinks': Raj Patel takes Archie, Jughead, Betty and Veronica on a trip to India to visit his uncle's video game company! Will Archie's ever-prominent clumsiness lead to a premature 'game over' for the tour, or could it possibly inspire the 3-D animators to come up with a brand-new game? It's a 'high score' of an issue you won't want to miss!
